# Management Layer Rules

## Admin Operations

- All admin operations require proper authorization
- Log all administrative actions
- Validate admin inputs strictly
- Provide audit trails for sensitive operations

## Configuration Management

- Configuration should be environment-specific
- Never commit secrets or credentials
- Use configuration validation on startup
- Support configuration hot-reload when possible

## User Management

- Implement proper password hashing
- Enforce password policies
- Support user role assignment
- Track user activity for security

## Monitoring

- Log important system events
- Use structured logging
- Include correlation IDs for request tracing
- Monitor system health metrics

## Health Checks

- Implement health check endpoints
- Check database connectivity
- Verify external service availability
- Return appropriate status codes
